original: Ljunggren, Karl Gustaf, advokat, Jönköping, f. 21/2/89 i Jönköping av Johannes L. o. Gustava Pettersson. — Stud :ex. i Lund 07, jur. kand. i Sthlm 16. Res. t. Amerika 09-12, Afrika 25 samt de fl. länder i Europa. Egen adv:rör. i Vänersb. 25-36, i Jönköp. sed. 36. Led. av Sv :es adv:samf. sed. 25. Distr:- o. stud :mästerskap i allm. idr. Hobbies: segling, skytte, jakt.
translated: Ljunggren, Karl Gustaf, attorney, Jönköping, b. 21/2/89 in Jönköping to Johannes L. and Gustava Pettersson. — Studied at Lund University until 1907, received a law degree in Stockholm in 1916. Traveled to America from 1909-1912, Africa in 1925, and various countries in Europe. Had his own law firm in Vänersborg from 1925-1936, and in Jönköping since 1936. Member of the Swedish Bar Association since 1925. Involved in organizing and participating in sports competitions. Hobbies include sailing, shooting, and hunting.
